parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle loses power or speed
the transmission warning light illuminates
and the vehicle makes unusual noises when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission warning light illuminates
the engine RPMs increase or decrease erratically
and the vehicle makes unusual noises when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission speed sensor can cause the vehicle to jerk, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle loses power or speed
the transmission warning light illuminates
and the vehicle makes unusual noises when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle makes unusual noises when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion steering can cause the steering wheel to become extremely difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the steering wheel seizes
the power steering fails
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel makes a grinding or popping noise
the steering wheel becomes loose or wobbly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the driver is unable to stop the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without pressing the accelerator pedal
the engine surges or revs up to high RPM
the vehicle moves forward even when the brake pedal is pressed
and the driver experiences difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty throttle body can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle drives very slowly when the accelerator pedal is depressed
and the vehicle rapidly accelerates after hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the vehicle becomes stuck in gear or fails to shift properly.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate
the transmission slips or hesitates
and the vehicle becomes stuck in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speed sensor can cause the vehicle to enter limp mode, leading to loss of power and control, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle decelerates or enters limp mode
all warning lights on the instrumental panel illuminate
and the vehicle's speedometer and odometer may malfunction.
